39int
40nv50_disp_root_scanoutpos(NV50_DISP_MTHD_V0)
41{
42 struct nvkm_device *device = disp->base.engine.subdev.device;
43 const u32 blanke = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x610aec + (head * 0x540));
44 const u32 blanks = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x610af4 + (head * 0x540));
45 const u32 total = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x610afc + (head * 0x540));
46 union {
47 struct nv04_disp_scanoutpos_v0 v0;
48 } *args = data;
49 int ret;
50
51 nvif_ioctl(object, "disp scanoutpos size %d\n", size);
52 if (nvif_unpack(args->v0, 0, 0, false)) {
53 nvif_ioctl(object, "disp scanoutpos vers %d\n",
54 args->v0.version);
55 args->v0.vblanke = (blanke & 0xffff0000) >> 16;
56 args->v0.hblanke = (blanke & 0x0000ffff);
57 args->v0.vblanks = (blanks & 0xffff0000) >> 16;
58 args->v0.hblanks = (blanks & 0x0000ffff);
59 args->v0.vtotal = ( total & 0xffff0000) >> 16;
60 args->v0.htotal = ( total & 0x0000ffff);
61 args->v0.time[0] = ktime_to_ns(ktime_get());
62 args->v0.vline = /* vline read locks hline */
63 nvkm_rd32(device, 0x616340 + (head * 0x800)) & 0xffff;
64 args->v0.time[1] = ktime_to_ns(ktime_get());
65 args->v0.hline =
66 nvkm_rd32(device, 0x616344 + (head * 0x800)) & 0xffff;
67 } else
68 return ret;
69
70 return 0;
71}
72
73static int
74nv50_disp_root_mthd_(struct nvkm_object *object, u32 mthd, void *data, u32 size)
75{
76 union {
77 struct nv50_disp_mthd_v0 v0;
78 struct nv50_disp_mthd_v1 v1;
79 } *args = data;
80 struct nv50_disp_root *root = nv50_disp_root(object);
81 struct nv50_disp *disp = root->disp;
82 const struct nv50_disp_func *func = disp->func;
83 struct nvkm_output *outp = NULL;
84 struct nvkm_output *temp;
85 u16 type, mask = 0;
86 int head, ret;
87
88 if (mthd != NV50_DISP_MTHD)
89 return -EINVAL;
90
91 nvif_ioctl(object, "disp mthd size %d\n", size);
92 if (nvif_unpack(args->v0, 0, 0, true)) {
93 nvif_ioctl(object, "disp mthd vers %d mthd %02x head %d\n",
94 args->v0.version, args->v0.method, args->v0.head);
95 mthd = args->v0.method;
96 head = args->v0.head;
97 } else
98 if (nvif_unpack(args->v1, 1, 1, true)) {
99 nvif_ioctl(object, "disp mthd vers %d mthd %02x "
100 "type %04x mask %04x\n",
101 args->v1.version, args->v1.method,
102 args->v1.hasht, args->v1.hashm);
103 mthd = args->v1.method;
104 type = args->v1.hasht;
105 mask = args->v1.hashm;
106 head = ffs((mask >> 8) & 0x0f) - 1;
107 } else
108 return ret;
109
110 if (head < 0 || head >= disp->base.head.nr)
111 return -ENXIO;
112
113 if (mask) {
114 list_for_each_entry(temp, &disp->base.outp, head) {
115 if ((temp->info.hasht == type) &&
116 (temp->info.hashm & mask) == mask) {
117 outp = temp;
118 break;
119 }
120 }
121 if (outp == NULL)
122 return -ENXIO;
123 }
124
125 switch (mthd) {
126 case NV50_DISP_SCANOUTPOS:
127 return func->head.scanoutpos(object, disp, data, size, head);
128 default:
129 break;
130 }
131
132 switch (mthd * !!outp) {
133 case NV50_DISP_MTHD_V1_DAC_PWR:
134 return func->dac.power(object, disp, data, size, head, outp);
135 case NV50_DISP_MTHD_V1_DAC_LOAD:
136 return func->dac.sense(object, disp, data, size, head, outp);
137 case NV50_DISP_MTHD_V1_SOR_PWR:
138 return func->sor.power(object, disp, data, size, head, outp);
139 case NV50_DISP_MTHD_V1_SOR_HDA_ELD:
140 if (!func->sor.hda_eld)
141 return -ENODEV;
142 return func->sor.hda_eld(object, disp, data, size, head, outp);
143 case NV50_DISP_MTHD_V1_SOR_HDMI_PWR:
144 if (!func->sor.hdmi)
145 return -ENODEV;
146 return func->sor.hdmi(object, disp, data, size, head, outp);
147 case NV50_DISP_MTHD_V1_SOR_LVDS_SCRIPT: {
148 union {
149 struct nv50_disp_sor_lvds_script_v0 v0;
150 } *args = data;
151 nvif_ioctl(object, "disp sor lvds script size %d\n", size);
152 if (nvif_unpack(args->v0, 0, 0, false)) {
153 nvif_ioctl(object, "disp sor lvds script "
154 "vers %d name %04x\n",
155 args->v0.version, args->v0.script);
156 disp->sor.lvdsconf = args->v0.script;
157 return 0;
158 } else
159 return ret;
160 }
161 break;
162 case NV50_DISP_MTHD_V1_SOR_DP_PWR: {
163 struct nvkm_output_dp *outpdp = nvkm_output_dp(outp);
164 union {
165 struct nv50_disp_sor_dp_pwr_v0 v0;
166 } *args = data;
167 nvif_ioctl(object, "disp sor dp pwr size %d\n", size);
168 if (nvif_unpack(args->v0, 0, 0, false)) {
169 nvif_ioctl(object, "disp sor dp pwr vers %d state %d\n",
170 args->v0.version, args->v0.state);
171 if (args->v0.state == 0) {
172 nvkm_notify_put(&outpdp->irq);
173 outpdp->func->lnk_pwr(outpdp, 0);
174 atomic_set(&outpdp->lt.done, 0);
175 return 0;
176 } else
177 if (args->v0.state != 0) {
178 nvkm_output_dp_train(&outpdp->base, 0, true);
179 return 0;
180 }
181 } else
182 return ret;
183 }
184 break;
185 case NV50_DISP_MTHD_V1_PIOR_PWR:
186 if (!func->pior.power)
187 return -ENODEV;
188 return func->pior.power(object, disp, data, size, head, outp);
189 default:
190 break;
191 }
192
193 return -EINVAL;
194}

196static int
197nv50_disp_root_dmac_new_(const struct nvkm_oclass *oclass,
198 void *data, u32 size, struct nvkm_object **pobject)
199{
200 const struct nv50_disp_dmac_oclass *sclass = oclass->priv;
201 struct nv50_disp_root *root = nv50_disp_root(oclass->parent);
202 return sclass->ctor(sclass->func, sclass->mthd, root, sclass->chid,
203 oclass, data, size, pobject);
204}

206static int
207nv50_disp_root_pioc_new_(const struct nvkm_oclass *oclass,
208 void *data, u32 size, struct nvkm_object **pobject)
209{
210 const struct nv50_disp_pioc_oclass *sclass = oclass->priv;
211 struct nv50_disp_root *root = nv50_disp_root(oclass->parent);
212 return sclass->ctor(sclass->func, sclass->mthd, root, sclass->chid,
213 oclass, data, size, pobject);
214}
215
216static int
217nv50_disp_root_child_get_(struct nvkm_object *object, int index,
218 struct nvkm_oclass *sclass)
219{
220 struct nv50_disp_root *root = nv50_disp_root(object);
221
222 if (index < ARRAY_SIZE(root->func->dmac)) {
223 sclass->base = root->func->dmac[index]->base;
224 sclass->priv = root->func->dmac[index];
225 sclass->ctor = nv50_disp_root_dmac_new_;
226 return 0;
227 }
228
229 index -= ARRAY_SIZE(root->func->dmac);
230
231 if (index < ARRAY_SIZE(root->func->pioc)) {
232 sclass->base = root->func->pioc[index]->base;
233 sclass->priv = root->func->pioc[index];
234 sclass->ctor = nv50_disp_root_pioc_new_;
235 return 0;
236 }
237
238 return -EINVAL;
239}
240
241static int
242nv50_disp_root_fini_(struct nvkm_object *object, bool suspend)
243{
244 struct nv50_disp_root *root = nv50_disp_root(object);
245 root->func->fini(root);
246 return 0;
247}
248
249static int
250nv50_disp_root_init_(struct nvkm_object *object)
251{
252 struct nv50_disp_root *root = nv50_disp_root(object);
253 return root->func->init(root);
254}
255
256static void *
257nv50_disp_root_dtor_(struct nvkm_object *object)
258{
259 struct nv50_disp_root *root = nv50_disp_root(object);
260 nvkm_ramht_del(&root->ramht);
261 nvkm_gpuobj_del(&root->instmem);
262 return root;
263}
264
265static const struct nvkm_object_func
266nv50_disp_root_ = {
267 .dtor = nv50_disp_root_dtor_,
268 .init = nv50_disp_root_init_,
269 .fini = nv50_disp_root_fini_,
270 .mthd = nv50_disp_root_mthd_,
271 .ntfy = nvkm_disp_ntfy,
272 .sclass = nv50_disp_root_child_get_,
273};
274
275int
276nv50_disp_root_new_(const struct nv50_disp_root_func *func,
277 struct nvkm_disp *base, const struct nvkm_oclass *oclass,
278 void *data, u32 size, struct nvkm_object **pobject)
279{
280 struct nv50_disp *disp = nv50_disp(base);
281 struct nv50_disp_root *root;
282 struct nvkm_device *device = disp->base.engine.subdev.device;
283 int ret;
284
285 if (!(root = kzalloc(sizeof(*root), GFP_KERNEL)))
286 return -ENOMEM;
287 *pobject = &root->object;
288
289 nvkm_object_ctor(&nv50_disp_root_, oclass, &root->object);
290 root->func = func;
291 root->disp = disp;
292
293 ret = nvkm_gpuobj_new(disp->base.engine.subdev.device, 0x10000, 0x10000,
294 false, NULL, &root->instmem);
295 if (ret)
296 return ret;
297
298 return nvkm_ramht_new(device, 0x1000, 0, root->instmem, &root->ramht);
299}
300
301void
302nv50_disp_root_fini(struct nv50_disp_root *root)
303{
304 struct nvkm_device *device = root->disp->base.engine.subdev.device;
305 /* disable all interrupts */
306 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x610024, 0x00000000);
307 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x610020, 0x00000000);
308}
309
310int
311nv50_disp_root_init(struct nv50_disp_root *root)
312{
313 struct nv50_disp *disp = root->disp;
314 struct nvkm_device *device = disp->base.engine.subdev.device;
315 u32 tmp;
316 int i;
317
318 /* The below segments of code copying values from one register to
319 * another appear to inform EVO of the display capabilities or
320 * something similar. NFI what the 0x614004 caps are for..
321 */
322 tmp = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x614004);
323 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x610184, tmp);
324
325 /* ... CRTC caps */
326 for (i = 0; i < disp->base.head.nr; i++) {
327 tmp = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x616100 + (i * 0x800));
328 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x610190 + (i * 0x10), tmp);
329 tmp = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x616104 + (i * 0x800));
330 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x610194 + (i * 0x10), tmp);
331 tmp = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x616108 + (i * 0x800));
332 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x610198 + (i * 0x10), tmp);
333 tmp = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x61610c + (i * 0x800));
334 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x61019c + (i * 0x10), tmp);
335 }
336
337 /* ... DAC caps */
338 for (i = 0; i < disp->func->dac.nr; i++) {
339 tmp = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x61a000 + (i * 0x800));
340 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x6101d0 + (i * 0x04), tmp);
341 }
342
343 /* ... SOR caps */
344 for (i = 0; i < disp->func->sor.nr; i++) {
345 tmp = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x61c000 + (i * 0x800));
346 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x6101e0 + (i * 0x04), tmp);
347 }
348
349 /* ... PIOR caps */
350 for (i = 0; i < disp->func->pior.nr; i++) {
351 tmp = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x61e000 + (i * 0x800));
352 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x6101f0 + (i * 0x04), tmp);
353 }
354
355 /* steal display away from vbios, or something like that */
356 if (nvkm_rd32(device, 0x610024) & 0x00000100) {
357 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x610024, 0x00000100);
358 nvkm_mask(device, 0x6194e8, 0x00000001, 0x00000000);
359 if (nvkm_msec(device, 2000,
360 if (!(nvkm_rd32(device, 0x6194e8) & 0x00000002))
361 break;
362 ) < 0)
363 return -EBUSY;
364 }
365
366 /* point at display engine memory area (hash table, objects) */
367 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x610010, (root->instmem->addr >> 8) | 9);
368
369 /* enable supervisor interrupts, disable everything else */
370 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x61002c, 0x00000370);
371 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x610028, 0x00000000);
372 return 0;
373}

375static const struct nv50_disp_root_func
376nv50_disp_root = {
377 .init = nv50_disp_root_init,
378 .fini = nv50_disp_root_fini,
379 .dmac = {
380 &nv50_disp_core_oclass,
381 &nv50_disp_base_oclass,
382 &nv50_disp_ovly_oclass,
383 },
384 .pioc = {
385 &nv50_disp_oimm_oclass,
386 &nv50_disp_curs_oclass,
387 },
388};

390static int
391nv50_disp_root_new(struct nvkm_disp *disp, const struct nvkm_oclass *oclass,
392 void *data, u32 size, struct nvkm_object **pobject)
393{
394 return nv50_disp_root_new_(&nv50_disp_root, disp, oclass,
395 data, size, pobject);
396}

398const struct nvkm_disp_oclass
399nv50_disp_root_oclass = {
400 .base.oclass = NV50_DISP,
401 .base.minver = -1,
402 .base.maxver = -1,
403 .ctor = nv50_disp_root_new,
404};
